column5: Dave, Talked to our officer up there. Lake ic ice free over to Burntwood Island in Twp 114 Rge 4. Please remember our officer is posted on the west side of the lake in Alberta.
Anyone from far north , how is the ice out looking this year we go up the 9th of June. Thanks in advance. Atlanta Dave
Dave, I have emailed our officer who is stationed up that way for an update. As soon as I hear I will post here.

Dave here is the latest The commercial fishing season on the lake is open which means basically all the ice is off on the Alberta side of the lake. However, there is an east wind today and some ice is being blown our way. Hope this helps.
John Thanks for the info if you hear anything new please post it . Atlanta Dave
Dave, Your going a little early this year, arn't you? Good Luck Report when you get back

Doc We have the 2nd week which is when we always go. Also we are the 3rd week this year . We are switching to the 3rd week from this year on out. Also he has no one the week before us this year so we are the 1st week of the camp being open. Atlanta Dave
Dave, Get a big one and talk lots of pics! Dave
Doc Dwight was fishing with one of our Athabasca group tues and wed on erie they got one smallie 7.1 lbs and 4 in the 6pound range. Not bad for 2 days. Will send you pics Atlanta Dave
Looking for any more up to date reports on ice out in the Athabasca area. Atlanta Dave
